#: ../../S/spamhaus.rst:5
msgid "spamhaus"
msgstr "spamhaus"

#: ../../S/spamhaus.rst:7
msgid "spam´hows, n\\."
msgstr "spam´hows, 名詞"

#: ../../S/spamhaus.rst:9
msgid ""
"Pejorative term for an internet service provider that permits or even "
"encourages :ref:`spam` mailings from its systems. The plural is spamhausen. "
"There is a web page devoted to `tracking spamhausen "
"<http://www.spamhaus.org/>`_."
msgstr ""
"自らのシステムからの\\ :ref:`spam`\\ "
"を許可、あるいは奨励さえするインターネットサービスプロバイダを指す蔑称。複数形はspamhausen。\\ `spamhausenを追跡する "
"<http://www.spamhaus.org/>`_\\ ことに捧げられたWebページがある。"

#: ../../S/spamhaus.rst:13
msgid ""
"The most notorious of the spamhausen was Sanford Wallace's Cyber Promotions "
"Inc., shut down by a lawsuit on 16 October 1997. The anniversary of the "
"shutdown is celebrated on Usenet as Spam Freedom Day, but lesser imitators "
"of the Spamford still infest various murky corners of the net. Since "
"prosecution of spammers became routine under the junk-fax laws and statues "
"specifically targeting spam, spamhausen have declined in relative "
"importance; today, hit-and-run attacks by spammers using :ref:`relay-rape` "
"and :ref:`throwaway-account`\\s on reputable ISPs seem to account for most "
"of the flow."
msgstr ""
"最も悪名高いspamhausenは、1997年10月16日に訴訟で閉鎖されたSanford WallaceのCyber Promotions "
"Inc.だった。閉鎖の記念日はUsenetでSpam Freedom "
"Day(スパム解放の日)として祝われるが、Spamfordの劣った模倣者たちは、いまだネットのさまざまな暗い片隅に巣食っている。ジャンクファクス法とスパムを特に標的とした制定法の下でスパマーの訴追が日常的になって以来、spamhausenの相対的な重要性は低下した。今日では、評判のよいISP上で\\"
" :ref:`relay-rape`\\ や\\ :ref:`throwaway-account`\\ "
"を使うスパマーによるひき逃げ攻撃が、流通の大半を占めているようだ。"
